25/08/2010
PODGORICA, Montenegro -- The Prosecutor's Office has filed charges against 21 people for abuse of office and bribery. 
The Supreme Court announced on Tuesday (August 24th) that among those charged are 15 customs officers and three police officers. 
They are accused of causing damages worth more than 20,000 euros to the budget between November 2009 and May of this year. 
(RTCG, Radio Free Europe, MINA - 24/08/10)
